Description: Part of the end-wall of the plastered wooden coffin of Mesehti; palace-façade decoration on the outer surface and Hieroglyphic text on both sides.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: Nicholson and Shaw, Ancient Egyptian Materials and Technology (Cambridge 2000), p. 114, 347
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 234)
